Add the validation to spring boot application
 
steps 1:-
    <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-validation</artifactId>
    </dependency>

 
step2:-
    use the validation annotation.  in Entity/ DTO  
    All the request coming to the controller class should be validated.
 
 
Validation Annotations Reference:
---------------------------------
 
| Field Type    | Annotation                  | Example                                      | Meaning                                |
|---------------|-----------------------------|----------------------------------------------|----------------------------------------|
| String        | @NotBlank                   | @NotBlank(message="Name required")           | Must not be null/empty/whitespace      |
| String        | @Size(min=2, max=50)        | @Size(min=2, max=50)                         | Length constraints                     |
| String        | @Pattern(regexp="^[A-Za-z]+$") | @Pattern(regexp="^[A-Za-z]+$")             | Regex validation                       |
| int / long    | @Min(18)                    | @Min(18)                                     | Minimum value                          |
| int / long    | @Max(65)                    | @Max(65)                                     | Maximum value                          |
| int / long    | @Positive                   | @Positive                                    | Must be > 0                            |
| double/float  | @DecimalMin("0.0")          | @DecimalMin("0.0")                           | Minimum decimal                        |
| double/float  | @DecimalMax("100.0")        | @DecimalMax("100.0")                         | Maximum decimal                        |
| double/float  | @Digits(integer=5,fraction=2) | @Digits(integer=5, fraction=2)             | Precision control                      |
| Date          | @Past                       | @Past                                        | Must be before now                     |
| Date          | @Future                     | @Future                                      | Must be after now                      |
| Date          | @PastOrPresent              | @PastOrPresent                               | Must be ≤ now                          |
| Date          | @FutureOrPresent            | @FutureOrPresent                             | Must be ≥ now                          |
| Boolean       | @AssertTrue                 | @AssertTrue                                  | Must be true                           |
| Boolean       | @AssertFalse                | @AssertFalse                                 | Must be false                          |
| Any Object    | @NotNull                    | @NotNull                                     | Must not be null                       |
| Nested Object | @Valid                      | @Valid private Address address;              | Cascade validation to nested objects   |
 
 
step3:
    add @valid to RequestBody. 
    if any validation fails it will throw this exception MethodArgumentNotValidException.
 

4.create a handler for MethodArgumentNotValidException.  
 
   
	@ExceptionHandler(exception = MethodArgumentNotValidException.class)
	public ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> handleValidationException(MethodArgumentNotValidException exception)
	{
		Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();
		for(FieldError fieldError : exception.getBindingResult().getFieldErrors())
		{
			errors.put(fieldError.getField(), fieldError.getDefaultMessage());
		}

		return new ResponseEntity<Map<String,String>>(errors, HttpStatus.BAD_REQUEST);
	}

